This kid-friendly, family favorite recipe is a delicious twist on dinnertime. 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breasts cut into 1-inch by 3-inch strips 1 cup buttermilk 2 cups Lay’s Cheddar and Sour Cream Flavor Potato Chips 2 Tbsp buttermilk 1 large egg This recipe and others are available on the Frito-Lay website at www.fritolay.com/recipes. Take 4 to 5 strips of chicken, allow excess buttermilk to drip off, dip into egg mixture, then add to the plastic bag with the potato chips. 5. Toss to coat thoroughly, repeat with remaining chicken. 6. Transfer the coated chicken to the prepared pan. 7. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden and crisp on the outside and cooked through. Saturated fat content of this product is 1 g per 1 oz serving. Total fat content of Lay's Potato Chips made with sunflower oil is 10 g per 1 oz serving). Title: Lay's Kettle Cooked Potato Chips, Sea Salt and Vinegar, 8.5 Ounce (Pack of 4)
Description:
When it comes to kettle style chips, nothing beats the thick, home-style crunch of LAY’S Kettle Cooked Potato Chips. LAY’S Sea Salt & Vinegar Flavored Kettle Cooked Potato Chips are a crunchy thick slice of home-style taste. Each lip-smacking batch is uniquely made to deliver a hearty crunch that will surely satisfy even the most discerning potato chip aficionado. Take a minute to relax, unwind, and savor–one delicious bite at a time. LAY’S Sea Salt & Vinegar Flavored Kettle Cooked Potato Chips are made with a perfect blend of sea salt and a measure of bright tangy vinegar for kick; few flavors pair so perfectly with potato chips. Step 1. LAY'S starts with quality farm-grown potatoes and slices them nice and thick. Step 2. Small batches of thick-sliced potatoes go into a kettle. Step 3. A unique, slow cooking process creates extra-crunchy potato chips. Step 4. Authentic, real ingredients and delicious flavors are then added. Step 5. Finished potato chips are immediately packaged. Step 6. Grab a handful and enjoy every last crunchy bite. From the everyday snack to the impromptu get-together, LAY’S Sea Salt & Vinegar Flavored Kettle Cooked Potato Chips are the perfect addition to any occasion. And with LAY’S take-home bags, you can share more delicious flavor by the handful. In 1932, Herman Lay, the founder of the H.W. Lay Co., started selling LAY’S potato chips right out of his Ford Model A. Now, LAY’S chips are still being made with genuine, trusted ingredients. And after nearly a century in the “chip business,” we’re not stopping any time soon. Here at Frito-Lay, we continue to innovate so that we can provide reliable, well-crafted products that are as good as they are fun. 
Pack of four, 8.5 ounce (Total of 34 ounce). Kettle cooked potato chips, flavored with sea salt and vinegar, packed in a convenient take-home bag. Extra-crunchy, batch-cooked and flavored with the perfect blend of delicious sea salt and tangy vinegar. No gluten ingredients**

Title: Lay's Barbecue Flavored Potato Chips - 7.75oz
Description:
With a secret blend of flavorful barbeque spices and famous fresh taste, Lay's Barbecue flavored potato chips are a tasty tribute to the American backyard grilling tradition!

These crispy chips have a sweet and smoky flavor that's both fresh and inviting whether you savor the flavor as a side to burgers hot off the grill, or embrace spontaneity by crumbling them into a chicken salad to add some crunch and fun.

The sweet and smoky taste of Lay's Barbecue flavored potato chips offers the perfect, iconic flavor to satisfy all your snacking needs. Title: Lay's Potato Chips, Sour Cream and Onion,Family Size,10 Ounce
Description:
Product description Each bag of LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Potato Chips is a little reminder of how good the simple things are. LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Potato Chips have been a flavor favorite for many years. The tart sour cream taste and onion flavor are blended to create the perfect seasoning that people have come to love. Where there are smiles, there are LAY’S Potato Chips It’s funny how something as simple as a bowl of chips can bring people together. Whether it’s party time or family time, everyone loves gathering around the chip bowl. With conversations swirling and laughter all around, each bag of LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Potato Chips is an opportunity to make memories. From the everyday snack to the impromptu get-togethers, LAY’S chips are the perfect addition to any occasion. And with LAY’S big bags you can share more delicious flavor by the handful. A little Frito-Lay history In 1932, Herman Lay, the founder of the H.W. Lay Co., started selling LAY’S potato chips right out of his Ford Model A. Now, 75 years later, LAY’S chips are still being made with genuine, trusted ingredients. And after nearly a century in the “chip business,” we’re not stopping anytime soon. Here at Frito-Lay, we continue to innovate so that we can provide reliable, well-crafted products that are as good as they are fun. Enjoy the traditional taste of LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Potato Chips all on their own, pair them with your favorite dip, or mix things up with your own culinary creation. The trusted taste of LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Potato Chips makes them a perfect ingredient for many delicious recipes. Recipe inspiration Take the tasty adventure beyond the bag, and use LAY’S chips to whip up something delicious enough to gather the whole family around. LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Chicken Chips Description: Give dinner a tasty twist with LAY’S Sour Cream and Onion Flavor Potato Chips. Ingredients: 2 – 8 oz chicken breasts ½ cup flour 4 eggs, beaten 1 large bag LAY'S Sour Cream & Onion Flavored Potato Chips, crushed fine Instructions: 1. Between 2 sheets of plastic wrap, pound chicken breast with a mallet to a ¼-inch thickness. 2. Remove the top layer of plastic wrap, and dust the flattened chicken breasts with flour. 3. Use a brush to lightly brush the egg onto the floured breasts until coated. 4. Place chicken breasts, egg side down, onto a baking sheet lined with a bed of crushed LAY'S chips. 5. Dust the bare side of the chicken breasts with flour, brush them with egg until coated, and then cover them with crushed LAY'S Sour Cream & Onion Flavored Potato Chips. 6. With a small rolling pin, roll the chip-covered chicken breasts to approximately ¼-inch thickness. 7. Using a round cookie cutter stamp out the chicken “chips.” 8. Place chicken chips on a sheet pan and bake at 325°F for 10 minutes or until an internal temperature reaches 165°F. This recipe and others are available on the Frito-Lay website at www.fritolay.com/recipes. Disclosure: Frito-Lay is not liable or responsible for the outcome of any recipes from this website, as the ingredients used cannot be controlled nor can the environment where the recipe is made.

These delightfully crispy and wavy chips are infused with the refreshing taste of tzatziki, a classic Greek yogurt and cucumber dip. Title: lay s baked potato crisps original 11 oz
Description:
The perfectly crispy chip that has been America's favorite snack for more than 75 years. Wherever celebrations and good times happen, the Lay's brand will be there. With flavors almost as rich as our history, we have a chip or crisp flavor guaranteed to bring a smile on your face. Lays Classic potato chips are the perfect snack for any occasion. Provide the perfect portion size and classic taste to keep your customers, colleagues, and family happy. From store shelves, to the pantry, to the lunch box, all you have to do is grab a pack and go! Frito-Lay’s line of baked snacks are baked, not fried, to give you the great taste you’ve come to love with Frito-Lay snacks. On top of that, baked snacks offer less fat than regular potato chips. PepsiCo is one of the world’s leading food and beverage companies serving more than 200 countries and territories around the world. For more than 50 years, as tastes, trends and lifestyles have changed, PepsiCo has evolved with them. Title: Frito-Lay Baked Mix Variety Pack (30 ct.)
Description:
Discover the lighter side of Frito-Lay with the Frito-Lay Baked Mix Variety Pack. Frito-Lay’s line of Baked snacks are baked, not fried, to give you the great taste you’ve come to love with Frito-Lay snacks. The Baked Variety Pack provides the perfect portion size and variety to keep your entire family happy. No matter what the occasion, from the pantry, to your next party with friends, to the lunch box, all you have to do is grab a pack and go! The individually wrapped bags are great for snacking on-the-go. Frito-Lay Oven Baked Chips Variety Mix Frito-Lay chips are known for their bold flavors and fantastic crunch. Most chips are fried to get that same taste and texture, which adds fat and calories. Frito-Lay's Baked Chips are just as delicious as the original recipe, with most varieties containing under 150 calories per serving. On top of that, Baked snacks offer 65% less fat than regular potato chips and 50% less fat than regular cheese-flavored snacks. Popular Flavors Frito-Lay variety packs include multiple bags of its most loved flavors. This pack includes five varieties to choose from: 8 bags of Lay’s Original Potato Crisps, 8 bags of Cheetos Crunchy Cheese Flavored Snacks, 6 bags of Lay’s Barbecue Flavored Potato Crisps, 4 bags of Lay’s Sour Cream & Onion Flavored Potato Crisps and 4 bags of Baked Ruffles Cheddar & Sour Cream Flavored Potato Crisps.
Frito-Lay Baked Mix Variety Pack (30 ct.)
